snippet.textDisplay:
Wilder is overrated, no style or class about him. Throws punches like a windmill. Pretty sure thats not taught in most gyms. Honestly it's no wonder he doesnt look good in fights until he lands a bomb, very misleading.


Put him in against fighters from the 70's, 80's and 90's and he'd be shown up for what he is. Boxers back then could box and hit hard. Real hard hitters include Tyson, Foreman, Tua, Lewis, even further back Shavers, Joe Louis. These guys threw sledgehammers with accuracy rather than go full pelt for 5 wild punches in the hope one lands. If a Lennox Lewis type was around today he'd destroy Wilder. If Fury can land better, harder shots like he's training for then my money is on him.
